Yesterday was great, First period I took a test which I didn't "finish" (lol) that way I could study over the weekend. Second period, Ms. Crawford and Ms. Guisti were having "OUR CLASS RULES" Wars. Ms. Crawford was like.. Ok I dare someone to go run into Ms. Guisti's class and be like "Ms. Crawfords class is the best!" and run out.. so Brennan and Kyle did... A few minutes later 2 of her students came in (they sounded soo enthused... *not) and said "Ms. Guisti told us to tell you our class is better." So then we sent like 10 people over there with pompoms and they did a little cheer for Ms. Crawfords class.... and then... lmao Ms. Guisti's whole class came over and Ms. Crawford locked her hallway door and ran to lock the courtyard door... she was going so fast I told TaLeisha "She's going to lock herself out." Well.. She didn't have to.. she successfully locked the door, and then Logan pulled it shut on her... she was out there screaming NOO NOO LET ME IN.. LMFAO and then all we hear is MR. SIMON IS COMING.. MR. SIMON IS COMING... and we let Ms. Crawford back in and opened the other door and guess who was there... MR. SIMON! OMFG.. It was hilarious... Ms. Crawford was like.. "We are all pumped up for the Pep Rally" and Mr. Simon didn't even care.. But still Ms. Crawford had to go through all the Mr. Simon crap.. so therefore, I think we won! Yay.. Go Ms. Crawfords (2nd period) Class!! Oh ya.. and Juniors totally kicked butt at the pep rally... JUNIORS RULE To bad all the pep rallies are fixed.. Last night my cousin Rachel (15) and Kristina (8) came over. Me, Rachel, Kameron, Kristina and Sissy were all jammin to MC Hammer. Rachel and I were trying to teach the kids how to do the "Runnin Man" it didn't go as planned, but I think part of the reason is because we can't do it either.. lmao Ahh... Whatta day... Lets do it again sometime!
